<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Class Balance<br>
<br>
 <br>
<br>
We're still planning to take a look at improving the damage capabilities of melee classes, as they've fallen behind their magic-using counterparts at the very high end of the game.  Finding the proper solutions for this situation will take some time.  Some options being considered are:<br>
<br>
 <br>
<br>
Improve melee damage-increasing disciplines <br>
<br>
Improve Planes of Power melee weapons <br>
<br>
 <br>
<br>
Additionally, we're looking at the concerns from players about their spells, and changing them where appropriate.  The goal here is to remove annoying issues with spells, not necessarily to increase caster power overall.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
In response to this, I sent the following feedback to Sony.  If you have ideas regarding this, OR if you like the ideas I proposed here, please submit them to Sony before they gimpify every old item in the game.  New items are nice.  Weapon upgrades are nice.  But the balance should start where the problems begin (around level 30 or so) and not when you reach the elemental planes.<br>
<br>
Trascript follows.<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
I noticed that you intend to change melee combat disciplines OR improve melee weapons to compensate for the lowered power of those classes.<br>
<br>
While I agree that there are some balancing problems, the solution is NOT to force 100% of the player base to acquire a specific weapon in order to meet a basic standard.<br>
<br>
If you increase the power of specific weapons in everquest, you will only be making all other weapons obsolete save those that you enhance.  If you give us disciplines (I play a 65 shadow knight) to increase melee output, it's like using a cork to plug a cracked dam.<br>
<br>
I would like to suggest that rather than to use those two methods, that you consider increasing the damage bonus from weapons based on the CLASS and by weapon type.<br>
<br>
For instance, a warrior wielding a weapon that is flagged as WAR ONLY would yield a much higher damage bonus by equipping said weapon.  The same warrior could pick up a weapon that is WAR, PAL, SHD, RNG and would have a slightly higher damage bonus than a PAL OR SHD but not as high as he gets from wielding a WAR only weapon.<br>
<br>
You might also consider giving SOME classes the ability to specialize in a weapon type (much like casters get for spells) so that when they are weilding a weapon they specialize in, they gain a damage bonus modifier.  <br>
<br>
Warriors presently have the same damage bonus for 1h and 2h weapons as hybrids.  They are supposed to be the MASTERS of weaponry, yet their ability to do damage with them is no greater than their hybrid counterparts... but hybrids get spells that augment their damage output by upwards of 50 damage per second in some encounters.<br>
<br>
Since we're on the topic of balancing, how about changing the effect of &quot;TAUNT&quot; so that instead of having a chance of putting you at the top of the hate list, that it ADDS HATE (like enraging blow) for the taunter... EVERY TIME.  Aggro control in groups without a hybrid tank, or a warrior with an enraging blow weapon is downright pathetic these days.<br>
<br>
Thanks. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.beaumontmachine.com/Assets/blindsig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
